The chairman of Abaji Area Council, Alhaji Abdulrahman Ajiya, has urged residents of the council to ensure they exposed criminals in their midst. Ajiya, who was speaking when he paid a Sallah homage to the Ona of Abaji at his palace, yesterday, also called on residents to cooperate with security agencies by giving them useful information that would lead to the arrest of suspected criminals in the area. He said protection of lives and property of residents of the area was one of the cardinal points of his administration. Also speaking, the Ona of Abaji, Alhaji Adamu Baba Yunusa, called on parents to ensure they enrolled their children in school so that they become useful to themselves and the society. He stressed the need for residents to live in peace with, as no society would develop without unity and peace among the people. I’ve built projects across political wards – Abaji chairman Ona of Abaji demands more logistics support for police I will not compromise peace, security - Abaji chairman Dear Esteemed reader, As part of our drive to keep improving the content of our newspaper, we are conducting a readership survey to enable us serve you better. Kindly take two minutes of your time to fill in this questionnaire. Thank you for your time. Click here to begin